# Astro SEO

Canonical layout: `@src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`. Site defaults: `@src/data/site.ts`. Config: `@astro.config.mjs`.

## Every page

- Pass unique `title` and `description` into `BaseLayout` (see `@src/pages/index.astro`).
- Layout must emit: canonical link, `robots`, Open Graph, Twitter card, theme-color, favicon/apple-touch-icon.
- Set `site` in `astro.config.mjs`. Keep `@astrojs/sitemap` and `@src/pages/robots.txt.ts` wired to that site URL.

## URLs and images

- Build absolute OG/schema image URLs from `Astro.site` (or `site.url`), never relative-only social URLs.
- Prefer `getImage()` / optimized asset URLs for schema images when the source is an imported asset.

## Structured data

- Business/marketing pages: JSON-LD `@graph` (e.g. ProfessionalService, WebSite, Person) matching BaseLayout.
- Keep business facts (name, email, locale, areaServed) in `@src/data/site.ts` so schema and UI stay in sync.

```astro
<!-- ❌ BAD: page with only a <title>, no description/canonical/OG -->
<!-- ✅ GOOD: <BaseLayout title="…" description="…">…</BaseLayout> -->
```
